olive oil
2 potato
1 tomato
1 carrot
1 bunch dill
1 packet Dijon mustard
½ tbs honey
½ tbs water
2 packet Beef Rump
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
¼ tsp salt
½ tbs white wine vinegar
1 bag salad leaves

Bring a medium saucepan of water to the boil. Cut the potato into bite-sized chunks. Cook the potato in the boiling water until easily pierced with a knife, 10-12 minutes. Drain and return to the saucepan. Cover to keep warm.

While the potato is cooking, slice the tomato into wedges. Grate the carrot. Roughly chop the dill. In a small bowl, combine the Dijon mustard, honey and water. Set aside.

If you're cooking double the beef rump, cook in batches for the best results. Heat a large frying pan over a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Season the beef rump on both sides with salt and pepper. When the oil is hot, cook the steak for 3-4 minutes on each side for medium or until cooked to your liking. Remove the pan from the heat, then add the honey-mustard glaze and turn to coat the steak. Transfer to a plate and leave to rest for 5 minutes.

While the steak is resting, add the Greek-style yoghurt and dill to the cooked potato. Add the salt and season with pepper, then gently toss to combine. Set aside.

In a large bowl, combine the white wine vinegar and a drizzle of olive oil, then season with salt and pepper. Add the spinach & rocket mix, tomato and carrot. Toss to coat.

Slice the honey mustard steak. Divide the steak, creamy dill potatoes and the garden salad between plates.